The assembly index $A$ (from Volume III) quantifies the minimal number of recursive steps required to construct a molecule from basic building blocks. High $A$ values ($A > 15$) are unlikely to form abiotically within cosmological timescales.

This provides a potential life detection metric independent of specific biochemistry. The machine learning approach described in Chapter 48 essentially learns to recognize high-assembly patterns without explicitly calculating $A$.

